- Do you have routers in stock?$- Yes, but only the ones with poor signal reception.
- Why are the router antennas so long?$- So you can wave them around dramatically when the internet drops.
- Is your router energy efficient?$- Extremely - it saves power by shutting down at the worst possible moment.
- Why does the router overheat?$- Because the router is ashamed of its speed.
- Why does the router specs say "up to 300 Mbps"?$- Because "up to" is the operative phrase here.
